<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy — Apple Privacy Manifest for @pyrx/synapse-react-native.

    Apple requires every third-party SDK shipped in iOS apps after May 2024
    to declare:
      1. Which "required-reason APIs" it uses (Apple-defined buckets like
         UserDefaults, FileTimestamp, SystemBootTime, DiskSpace).
      2. Which data categories it collects + the linkage / tracking flags.

    This manifest is the wrapper-specific declaration. The customer's host
    app must also ship its own PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy describing
    end-user-visible data flows. The two get merged at build time and
    surfaced to App Store Connect for App Privacy Report.

    What the WRAPPER uses
    =====================
    - UserDefaults: NO. We touch no UserDefaults directly; the underlying
      PYRXSynapse SDK persists everything via the Keychain.
    - FileTimestamp: NO. The bridge does not read file timestamps.
    - SystemBootTime: NO. The bridge does not read system boot time.
    - DiskSpace: NO.

    What the UNDERLYING PYRXSynapse SDK uses
    ========================================
    The native PYRXSynapse pod does NOT yet ship its own PrivacyInfo
    (its podspec doesn't bundle one as of v0.1.1). When that lands, this
    file will need to be updated to mirror or aggregate. Until then, we
    declare a minimal manifest covering the categories that actually
    apply to the wrapper's own code:
      - NSPrivacyTracking = false (the SDK does not track for ads)
      - NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes = [] (every data type collected is
        declared by the customer's app, not the wrapper itself)

    Reference: https://developer.apple.com/documentation/bundleresources/privacy_manifest_files
-->
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypes</key>
    <array/>
    <key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes</key>
    <array/>
    <key>NSPrivacyTracking</key>
    <false/>
    <key>NSPrivacyTrackingDomains</key>
    <array/>
</dict>
</plist>
